<div class="wide-dark-box">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>
        This Privacy Policy outlines the policies and procedures of the <strong>System for Healthcare Integration and Facility Tracking (S.H.I.F.T)</strong> regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal information when you use our system.
    </p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>
        We may collect the following types of information:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Information that can be used to identify you, such as your name, email address, phone number, and other contact details.</li>
        <li><strong>Health Information:</strong> Data related to patients' health, including medical history, treatment details, and vital signs.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about how the system is accessed and used, including your IP address, browser type, and the pages you visit.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>
        We use the collected information for the following purposes:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>To provide and maintain our system and services.</li>
        <li>To improve and personalize user experience.</li>
        <li>To analyze usage patterns and enhance system performance.</li>
        <li>To comply with legal obligations and ensure accountability.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Data Protection</h2>
    <p>
        We take the security of your personal information seriously and implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect it against unauthorized access, loss, or misuse.
    </p>

    <h2>Disclosure of Information</h2>
    <p>
        We do not sell or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may disclose your information in the following situations:
    </p>
    <ul>
        <li>To comply with legal requirements or respond to valid legal requests.</li>
        <li>To protect the rights and safety of our users or others.</li>
        <li>In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your Rights</h2>
    <p>
        You have the right to access, correct, or delete your personal information. If you wish to exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the information provided below.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
        We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page. We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
        If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong> support@shift-hospital.com <br>
        <strong>Phone:</strong> (123) 456-7890
    </p>
